    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="man_ej.00021_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="center"><handShift rend="printed"/>Asylum for the Insane,</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">London,</name>
                    <date when="1880-01-19" rend="right"><handShift rend="manuscript"/><choice><abbr>Jan</abbr><expan>January</expan></choice> 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>80</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Walt</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I am going to ask a great favor of you&#8212;I want you to write me a sketch of your interior life&#8212;especially in relation to the conception and elaboration of "Leaves of Grass" The germanancy and path of such a product as "Leaves of Grass" is a <choice><orig>psycological</orig><reg>psychological</reg></choice> expression almost unique in the history of the race and some record of it ought to remain if possible&#8212;I need not explain any further what I want from you for you will understand at once what I mean and you must surely have 
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="man_ej.00022_large.jpg" type="verso"/>often thought of putting it upon record<ptr target="man.00002_n1"/></p>
            
            <p>I hope that you will take this matter into serious and favourable consideration</p>

            <closer>
                <salute rend="right">And I am</salute>
                <salute rend="right">Faithfully yours</salute>
                <signed rend="right">R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
